<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,424,1243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,289,424,450]" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">Diagnosis:—</emphasis>
Differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[434,594,424,450]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Erysiphaceae" genus="Podosphaera" kingdom="Fungi" order="Erysiphales" pageId="6" pageNumber="137" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="filipendulae">
<emphasis box="[434,594,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="137">P. filipendulae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its smaller peridium cells, aseptate, shorter and narrower appendages, and constant number of ascospores per ascus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
